{"title_page": "Ali G\u00f6kdemir", "text_new": "{{short description|Azerbaijani footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name        = Ali G\u00f6kdemir\n|image       = Ali G\u00f6kdemir 2012.jpg\n|caption     = With [[Azerbaijan national football team|Azerbaijan]] in 2012\n| fullname   = Ali Gutda G\u00f6kdemir<ref name=\"TFF.org\">{{cite web | url = http://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageId=526&kisiID=1678409 | title = AL\u0130 GUTDA G\u00d6KDEM\u0130R - Player Details TFF | publisher = TFF.org | accessdate = 6 February 2014}}</ref>\n|birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1991|9|17|df=y}}\n|birth_place = [[Schw\u00e4bisch Hall]], Germany\n|height      = {{height|m=1.84}}\n|position    = [[Defender (football)|Defender]]\n|currentclub = \n|clubnumber  = \n|youthyears1 = \n|youthclubs1 = Sportfreunde Schw\u00e4bisch Hall\n|youthyears2 = \n|youthclubs2 = TSV Ilshofen\n|youthyears3 = {{0|0000}}\u20132009\n|youthclubs3 = [[VfB Stuttgart]]\n|youthyears4 = 2009\u20132010\n|youthclubs4 = [[Hannover 96]]\n|years1      = 2010\u20132014\n|clubs1      = [[Hannover 96|Hannover 96 II]]\n|caps1       = 64\n|goals1      = 5\n|years2      = 2013\u20132014\n|clubs2      = [[Hannover 96]]\n|caps2       = 0\n|goals2      = 0\n|years3      = 2014\n|clubs3      = \u2192 [[Elaz\u0131\u011fspor]] (loan)\n|caps3       = 1\n|goals3      = 0\n|years4      = 2014\u20132015\n|clubs4      = [[Simurq PFK|Simurq]]\n|caps4       = 19\n|goals4      = 1\n|nationalyears1 = \n|nationalteam1  = [[Azerbaijan national under-21 football team|Azerbaijan U21]]\n|nationalcaps1  = \n|nationalgoals1 = \n|nationalyears2 = 2012\u20132015\n|nationalteam2  = [[Azerbaijan national football team|Azerbaijan]]\n|nationalcaps2  = 10\n|nationalgoals2 = 0\n|club-update = 31 May 2015 \n|ntupdate    = 1 August 2014 (UTC)\n}}\n\n'''Ali Gutda G\u00f6kdemir''' (born 17 September 1991) is an Azerbaijani retired international [[Association football|footballer]] who played as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]].<ref name=\"G\u00f6kdemir Retires\">{{cite web|title=\u0410\u043b\u0438 \u0413\u0435\u043a\u0434\u0435\u043c\u0438\u0440 \u0437\u0430\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0448\u0438\u043b \u043a\u0430\u0440\u044c\u0435\u0440\u0443|url=http://www.azerifootball.com/ru/17/news/29959.html|website=azerifootball.com|publisher=Azeri Football|accessdate=1 December 2015|language=Russian|date=1 December 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n\n===Club===\nG\u00f6kdemir has played club football in Germany for [[Hannover 96]] II.<ref name = \"NFT\">{{NFT player|pid=47647}}</ref><ref>{{Fussballdaten|goekdemirali}}</ref> For the second half of the 2013-14 season he was on loan to [[S\u00fcper Lig]] side [[Elaz\u0131\u011fspor]].\n\nIn July 2014, G\u00f6kdemir moved to [[Azerbaijan Premier League]] side [[Simurq PFK|Simurq]].<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ru:\u0418\u0437 \u0413\u0430\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0430 \u0432 \u0417\u0430\u0433\u0430\u0442\u0430\u043b\u044b|url=http://www.azerifootball.com/ru/13/news/24744.html|website=azerifootball.com|publisher=Azerifootball|accessdate=30 July 2014|language=Russian}}</ref> Despite having had a contract with Hannover until 2015,<ref>{{cite web|title=Hannover: G\u00f6kdemir in die T\u00fcrkei|url=http://www.spox.com/de/sport/fussball/bundesliga/1402/News/hannover-96-leiht-ali-goekdemir-bis-zum-saisonende-in-die-tuerkei-aus-sanica-boru-elazigspor.html|publisher=spox.com|accessdate=1 August 2014|language=German|date=3 February 2014}}</ref> he was released without a transfer fee.<ref>{{cite web|title=G\u00f6kdemir wechselt nach Aserbaidschan|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/wechselboerse/2014-15/1/tm-news--5519-8760-.html|publisher=kicker.de|accessdate=1 August 2014|language=German|date=28 July 2014}}</ref>\n\n===International===\nHe made his international debut for [[Azerbaijan national football team|Azerbaijan]] in 2012,<ref name = \"NFT\"/> and has appeared in FIFA World Cup qualifying matches.<ref>{{FIFA|359318}}</ref> He has also played for [[Azerbaijan national under-21 football team|Azerbaijan U21]].<ref>{{UEFA|250040485}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n\n===Club===\n{{updated|24 December 2014}}<ref>{{soccerway|ali-gokdemir/141415|accessdate=1 August 2014}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! colspan=3 | Club performance\n! colspan=2 | League\n! colspan=2 | Cup\n! colspan=2 | Continental\n! colspan=2 | Total\n|-\n! Season !! Club !! League\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n|-\n|[[2010\u201311 Regionalliga|2010-11]]<ref name=kicker1011/>||rowspan=\"4\"|[[Hannover 96|Hannover 96 II]]||rowspan=\"4\"|[[Regionalliga Nord]]\n|14||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||14||0\n|-\n|[[2011\u201312 Regionalliga|2011-12]]<ref name=kicker1112/>\n|19||1||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||19||1\n|-\n|[[2012\u201313 Regionalliga|2012-13]]<ref name=kicker1213/>\n|16||2||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||16||2\n|-\n|[[2013\u201314 Regionalliga|2013-14]]<ref name=kicker1314/>\n|15||2||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||15||2\n|-\n|[[2013\u201314 S\u00fcper Lig|2013-14]]||[[Elaz\u0131\u011fspor]] (loan)||[[S\u00fcper Lig]]||1||0||2||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||3||0\n|-\n|[[2014\u201315 Azerbaijan Premier League|2014-15]]||[[Simurq PFC|Simurq]]||[[Azerbaijan Premier League]]||19||1||1||1||colspan=\"2\"|-||20||2\n|-\n! rowspan=3 | Total\n! colspan=2 | Germany\n!64||5||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||64||5\n|-\n! colspan=2 | Turkey\n!1||0||2||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||3||0\n|-\n! colspan=2 | Azerbaijan\n!19||1||1||1||colspan=\"2\"|-||20||2\n|-\n! colspan=3 | Career total\n!84||6||3||1||colspan=\"2\"|-||87||7\n|}\n\n===International===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!colspan=3|[[Azerbaijan national football team|Azerbaijan]]\n|-\n|2012||7||0\n|-\n|2013||3||0\n|-\n|2014||0||0\n|-\n!Total||10||0\n|}\n''Statistics accurate as of match played 19 November 2013''<ref name = \"NFT\"/>\n\n==Personal life==\nHe is of Turkish descent.<ref name= \"tr.eurosport.com\">http://tr.eurosport.com/futbol/azerbaycan-dan-iki-turk_sto2896200/story.shtml</ref>\nG\u00f6kdemir retired from football in December 2015 due family reasons.<ref name=\"G\u00f6kdemir Retires\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n\n<ref name=kicker1011>{{Cite web |url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/intligen/startseite/2010-11/65515/vereinsspieler_goekdemir-ali.html |title= G\u00f6kdemir, Ali |publisher=kicker.de|language=German |accessdate=1 August 2014}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=kicker1112>{{Cite web |url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/intligen/startseite/2011-12/65515/vereinsspieler_goekdemir-ali.html |title= G\u00f6kdemir, Ali |publisher=kicker.de|language=German |accessdate=1 August 2014}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=kicker1213>{{Cite web |url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/intligen/startseite/2012-13/65515/vereinsspieler_goekdemir-ali.html |title= G\u00f6kdemir, Ali |publisher=kicker.de|language=German |accessdate=1 August 2014}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=kicker1314>{{Cite web |url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/intligen/startseite/2013-14/65515/vereinsspieler_goekdemir-ali.html |title= G\u00f6kdemir, Ali |publisher=kicker.de|language=German |accessdate=1 August 2014}}</ref>\n}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{NFT}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gokdemir, Ali}}\n[[Category:1991 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Schw\u00e4bisch Hall]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Baden-W\u00fcrttemberg]]\n[[Category:Azerbaijani footballers]]\n[[Category:Azerbaijani people of Turkish descent]]\n[[Category:Azerbaijan international footballers]]\n[[Category:Azerbaijan under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:German footballers]]\n[[Category:German people of Azerbaijani descent]]\n[[Category:German people of Turkish descent]]\n[[Category:Hannover 96 players]]\n[[Category:Hannover 96 II players]]\n[[Category:S\u00fcper Lig players]]\n[[Category:Elaz\u0131\u011fspor footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Azerbaijani expatriate footballers]]\n[[